call, and tell him to release Sheng Xiaoyun."

13
00:00:39,610 --> 00:00:45,390
Oh, and call you did. Many of you emailed
me your stories.

14
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:47,140
Here's just a taste.

15
00:00:47,140 --> 00:00:50,010
This one comes from viewer Sasha Ganapolsky.

16
00:00:50,010 --> 00:00:54,620
Yesterday I gave the officer a call which
he answered a few seconds later.

17
00:00:54,620 --> 00:00:58,879
My friend Lily speaks Mandarin so I asked
her to say "Release Sheng Xiaoyun."

18
00:00:58,879 --> 00:01:03,910
He then said, "Who are all of these people?"
with a voice like he's tired of it.

19
00:01:03,910 --> 00:01:07,369
Lily then said, "People who want justice in
China."

20
00:01:07,369 --> 00:01:11,159
He then said, "Ugh stop calling me!" And hung
up.

21
00:01:11,159 --> 00:01:13,560
Beautiful. Well done.

22
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:14,590
Very well done, in fact,

23
00:01:14,590 --> 00:01:19,500
because I just got word from Ben that his
mother-in-law was released yesterday.

24
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:23,920
And one of the police officers in the detention
center apparently told her they got a lot

25
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:26,960
of calls demanding they let her go.

26
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:27,900
Well done, my 50-Cent Army!

27
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:33,810
And although that warm, squishy feeling you
have inside right now is probably enough,

28
00:01:33,810 --> 00:01:38,850
